**What good looks like:** A complete matrix of every behavior type × customer segment showing: live on EVE, live on CBB only, pending, or not started. No ambiguity about what "all events" means.

**What I know:**
- **Collisions + Near-Collisions (Crash Pipeline):** Live, 100% SMB & MM, 60% bypass catching 99% collisions, 90%+ near-collisions
- **Hard Brakes:** Rollout starting 2026-04-13, full by 2026-04-30, target 80%+ bypass (AI-252)
- **SBV + SSV (CBB in EFS):** Live SMB with 80%+ bypass, MM/ENT rollout by 2026-03-31 (AI-24)
- **SBV + Distraction (EVE pipeline):** CBB changes deployed to Prod, DAG activation staged SMB → MM → ENT (AI-81)
- **Remaining DF behaviors:** Cell Phone, Yawning, Cam Obstruction, Smoking, Eating — foundation models trained, not in production EVE pipeline (AI-205)
- **Remaining RF behaviors:** Close Following, Sudden Speed Variation, Unsafe Lane Change, Unsafe Passing — foundation models trained, not in production (AI-205)
